# Creating an empty list to store file paths
files = []

# Looping through each year and find the corresponding CSV files
for year in years:
    file_pattern = folder_path + f'{year}-M.csv'  # Format file name pattern
    files.extend(glob.glob(file_pattern))  # Append all matching files to the list

# Printing the files that were found
print("Files found:", files)

# Loading all CSV files into a list of DataFrames
df_list = [pd.read_csv(file) for file in files]  # Read each file into a DataFrame

# Concatenating all DataFrames into one large DataFrame
data_2020_2025 = pd.concat(df_list, ignore_index=True)

# Displaying the shape of the final dataset (for debugging)
print("Final dataset shape:", data_2020_2025.shape)

data_final['sample.sampleDateTime'] = pd.to_datetime(data_final['sample.sampleDateTime'], errors='coerce')


data_final.sort_values(by="sample.sampleDateTime", inplace=True)

# 🟢 STEP 3: Backup datetime column BEFORE setting it as index
datetime_backup = data_final['sample.sampleDateTime'].copy()

group_cols = [
    "sample.sampledMaterialType.label",
    "sample.samplingPoint.easting",
    "sample.samplingPoint.northing"
]


def fill_ffill_bfill(group):
    cols_to_fill = group.columns.difference(group_cols)
    group[cols_to_fill] = group[cols_to_fill].ffill().bfill()
    return group


data_final = (
    data_final
    .groupby(group_cols, group_keys=False)
    .apply(fill_ffill_bfill)
    .reset_index(drop=True)
)


data_final['sample.sampleDateTime'] = datetime_backup.values


data_final.sort_values(by="sample.sampleDateTime", inplace=True)

            data_final

# Function to tag outliers using IQR method
def tag_outliers_iqr(df, col):
    Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    return (df[col] < lower) | (df[col] > upper)

# Apply the function to each key parameter and create a tag column
for col in key_parameters:
    if col in data_final.columns:  # Just in case
        outlier_col_name = f"{col}_is_outlier"
        data_final[outlier_col_name] = tag_outliers_iqr(data_final, col)

print("Outlier tagging complete! Here's a preview of the tagged dataset:")
print(data_final[[col for col in data_final.columns if 'is_outlier' in col]].head())

import streamlit as st
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Make sure column names are clean
data_final.columns = data_final.columns.str.strip()

# List of water quality parameters
key_parameters = [
    'O Diss %sat', 'Orthophospht', 'Ammonia(N)', 'Temp Water', 'pH',
    'Nitrite-N', 'Nitrate-N', 'TurbidityNTU', 'BOD ATU', 'Phosphorus-P'
]

# --- Plotting Functions ---

def plot_outlier_map(df, param):
    """Show map of outlier locations for selected parameter."""
    flag = f"{param}_is_outlier"
    if flag not in df.columns:
        st.warning(f"No outlier flag for {param}")
        return

    outliers = df[df[flag]]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.scatter(
        outliers['sample.samplingPoint.easting'],
        outliers['sample.samplingPoint.northing'],
        alpha=0.3, s=10, c='red'
    )
    ax.set_title(f"Outlier Locations: {param}")
    ax.set_xlabel("Easting")
    ax.set_ylabel("Northing")
    ax.grid(True)
    st.pyplot(fig)

def plot_outlier_frequency_per_water_type(df, parameters):
    """Bar chart: Outlier count per parameter and water type."""
    summary = {}
    for param in parameters:
        flag = f"{param}_is_outlier"
        if flag in df.columns:
            count_by_type = df[df[flag]].groupby('sample.sampledMaterialType.label').size()
            summary[param] = count_by_type

    outlier_freq_df = pd.DataFrame(summary).fillna(0).astype(int)

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6))
    outlier_freq_df.plot(kind='bar', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title("Outlier Frequency per Water Type")
    ax.set_ylabel("Number of Outliers")
    ax.set_xlabel("Water Type")
    ax.legend(title="Parameter", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    ax.grid(axis='y')
    st.pyplot(fig)

def plot_outlier_time_series(df, param):
    """Line chart: Outlier counts over time."""
    flag = f"{param}_is_outlier"
    if flag not in df.columns:
        st.warning(f"No outlier flag for {param}")
        return

    df_copy = df.copy()
    df_copy['sample.sampleDateTime'] = pd.to_datetime(df_copy['sample.sampleDateTime'])

    if 'sample.sampleDateTime' not in df_copy.columns:
        st.error("Missing 'sample.sampleDateTime' column.")
        return

    df_copy.set_index('sample.sampleDateTime', inplace=True)
    daily_counts = df_copy[flag].resample('D').sum()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))
    daily_counts.plot(ax=ax)
    ax.set_title(f"Daily Outlier Count: {param}")
    ax.set_xlabel("Date")
    ax.set_ylabel("Outlier Count")
    ax.grid(True)
    st.pyplot(fig)

# --- Streamlit UI ---
st.title("💧 Water Pollution Outlier Dashboard")

param = st.selectbox("Select a parameter to analyze:", key_parameters)

st.markdown("### 📍 Outlier Locations Map")
plot_outlier_map(data_final, param)

st.markdown("### 📊 Outlier Frequency by Water Type (All Parameters)")
plot_outlier_frequency_per_water_type(data_final, key_parameters)

st.markdown("### ⏰ Outlier Time Trend")
plot_outlier_time_series(data_final, param)

# Your water quality parameters
key_parameters = [
    'O Diss %sat', 'Orthophospht', 'Ammonia(N)', 'Temp Water', 'pH',
    'Nitrite-N', 'Nitrate-N', 'TurbidityNTU', 'BOD ATU', 'Phosphorus-P'
]

# Grouping by water type + coordinates
group_cols = [
    "sample.sampledMaterialType.label",
    "sample.samplingPoint.easting",
    "sample.samplingPoint.northing"
]

# ✅ Function to add rolling mean and lag features
def add_rolling_and_lag_features(df, param, group_cols, rolling_windows=[3], lags=[1]):
    """
    Add rolling mean and lag features for a given parameter per group.
    """
    df = df.sort_values('sample.sampleDateTime')  # Sort by time

    for window in rolling_windows:
        roll_col = f"{param}_rolling_mean_{window}"
        df[roll_col] = (
            df.groupby(group_cols)[param]
              .transform(lambda x: x.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean())
        )

    for lag in lags:
        lag_col = f"{param}_lag_{lag}"
        df[lag_col] = (
            df.groupby(group_cols)[param]
              .transform(lambda x: x.shift(lag))
        )

    return df

# ✅ Apply feature engineering to all key parameters
for param in key_parameters:
    data_final = add_rolling_and_lag_features(
        df=data_final,
        param=param,
        group_cols=group_cols,
        rolling_windows=[3],  # You can add [3, 5, 7] if you want
        lags=[1]              # Add more like [1, 2, 3] if useful
    )

print("✅ Rolling and lag features added for all parameters!")

from lightgbm import LGBMRegressor, early_stopping, log_evaluation
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

# Parameters to predict
key_parameters = [
    'O Diss %sat', 'Orthophospht', 'Ammonia(N)', 'Temp Water', 'pH',
    'Nitrite-N', 'Nitrate-N', 'TurbidityNTU', 'BOD ATU', 'Phosphorus-P'
]

# Columns to exclude
base_exclude = [
    'sample.sampleDateTime', 
    'sample.sampledMaterialType.label', 
    'sample.samplingPoint.easting', 
    'sample.samplingPoint.northing', 
    'season_label'
]

# Store results
results = {}

# Group by water type
for water_type, group_df in data_final.groupby('sample.sampledMaterialType.label'):
    print(f"\n🌊 Water Type: {water_type}")
    results[water_type] = {}

    for target in key_parameters:
        print(f"  🎯 Training model for: {target}")

        exclude_cols = base_exclude + [target]
        feature_cols = [col for col in group_df.columns if col not in exclude_cols]

        X = group_df[feature_cols]
        y = group_df[target]

        # Train-test split (no shuffle due to time)
        X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

        model = LGBMRegressor(
            objective='regression',
            learning_rate=0.05,
            num_leaves=31,
            random_state=42,
            n_estimators=1000
        )

        model.fit(
            X_train, y_train,
            eval_set=[(X_test, y_test)],
            callbacks=[
                early_stopping(stopping_rounds=20),
                log_evaluation(0)
            ]
        )

        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))
        r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)

        results[water_type][target] = {'RMSE': rmse, 'R2': r2}
        print(f"     ✅ RMSE: {rmse:.4f} | R²: {r2:.4f}")

# Final Summary
print("\n📈 Final Model Performance (per water type):")
for water_type, metrics in results.items():
    print(f"\n🌊 {water_type}")
    for param, score in metrics.items():
        print(f"{param.ljust(20)} | RMSE: {score['RMSE']:.4f} | R²: {score['R2']:.4f}")

import joblib
from lightgbm import LGBMRegressor, early_stopping, log_evaluation
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

# Parameters to predict
key_parameters = [
    'O Diss %sat', 'Orthophospht', 'Ammonia(N)', 'Temp Water', 'pH',
    'Nitrite-N', 'Nitrate-N', 'TurbidityNTU', 'BOD ATU', 'Phosphorus-P'
]

# Columns to exclude
base_exclude = [
    'sample.sampleDateTime',
    'sample.sampledMaterialType.label',
    'sample.samplingPoint.easting',
    'sample.samplingPoint.northing',
    'season_label'
]

# Set save path
save_path = "/Users/sofianebelbrik/Documents/water pollution/Pretrained_models/forecast"
os.makedirs(save_path, exist_ok=True)

# Create t+1 shifted targets
horizon = 1
for param in key_parameters:
    data_final[f'{param}_t_plus_{horizon}'] = data_final[param].shift(-horizon)

# Drop rows with missing targets
forecast_data = data_final.dropna(subset=[f'{param}_t_plus_{horizon}' for param in key_parameters])

# Init forecast result dict
forecast_results = {}

# 🔁 Train and Save per water type
for water_type in forecast_data['sample.sampledMaterialType.label'].unique():
    print(f"\n🌊 Forecasting t+{horizon} for: {water_type}")
    df_sub = forecast_data[forecast_data['sample.sampledMaterialType.label'] == water_type]
    
    forecast_results[water_type] = {}
    
    for target in key_parameters:
        print(f"📘 Training model for: {target} (t+{horizon})")
        
        target_col = f"{target}_t_plus_{horizon}"
        exclude_cols = base_exclude + [target, target_col]
        feature_cols = [col for col in df_sub.columns if col not in exclude_cols]

        X = df_sub[feature_cols]
        y = df_sub[target_col]

        X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

        model = LGBMRegressor(
            objective='regression',
            learning_rate=0.05,
            num_leaves=31,
            random_state=42,
            n_estimators=1000
        )

        model.fit(
            X_train, y_train,
            eval_set=[(X_test, y_test)],
            callbacks=[
                early_stopping(stopping_rounds=20),
                log_evaluation(0)
            ]
        )

        # 🔒 Save model
        clean_name = f"{water_type}_{target}_t+{horizon}".replace("/", "_")
        joblib.dump(model, os.path.join(save_path, f"{clean_name}.pkl"))

        # 📊 Evaluate
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))
        r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
        forecast_results[water_type][target] = {'RMSE': rmse, 'R2': r2}
        print(f"✅ Saved: {clean_name}.pkl | RMSE: {rmse:.4f} | R²: {r2:.4f}")

# 📊 Summary
for wt, results in forecast_results.items():
    print(f"\n🌊 Forecast Summary for {wt}")
    for param, score in results.items():
        print(f"{param.ljust(20)} | RMSE: {score['RMSE']:.4f} | R²: {score['R2']:.4f}")
